PCA’s Dr André Hattingh said, “We had a number of ‘super fans’, both big and small, who were very excited to hear that the Pumas were popping in for a visit to spread some joy among our children who needed a bit of cheering up.  “A few little ones were a bit sceptical about the mascot at first and made sure their moms stayed close by, but quickly realised that he is very huggable and friendly.  “Thank you for spending your day with us and making so many little children’s hearts happy,” he said. ALSO READ: Kruger Lowveld Tourism concerned about non-compliance with Covid-19 regulations